  (text "J2 PINOUT (1x6 2.54mm mates with UNO Q JSPI header):\\n  Pin 1: SPI_MOSI (from STM32U585 MCU)\\n  Pin 2: SPI_MISO (to STM32U585 MCU)\\n  Pin 3: SPI_SCK  (from STM32U585 MCU)\\n  Pin 4: CS_S3_MCU (GPIO10 active-LOW)\\n  Pin 5: GND\\n  Pin 6: +3V3 reference (do not draw current from UNO Q header)\\n\\nJ3 PINOUT (1x2 2.54mm debug UART):\\n  Pin 1: UART_TX (GPIO47) — S3 debug output at 115200 baud\\n  Pin 2: GND\\n  Use USB-UART adapter for bench debugging.\\n\\nCS_S3_MPU NOTE:\\n  QRB2210 MPU chip-select (GPIO0) is NOT on the shield.\\n  GPIO0 has 10kΩ pullup (R11) on PCB — boot-safe.\\n  CS_S3_MPU only used on Super Carrier via JMISC (B1)."
    (at 30 100 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "08a4c256-b6c5-449d-aef1-680c79343c8c")
  )
